abstract.label: Abstract
abstract.value: The Tisch School of the Arts (TSOA) was founded as a school of performing and media arts in 1965. Alumni include Spike Lee, Oliver Stone, Amy Heckerling, and Ang Lee. Much of the school's history is documented in the correspondence of the School's former Deans, Robert Oppenheim, Robert Corrigan and Theodore Hoffman. Additional records in the collection include annual reports, budgets, financial records, minutes, curricula, scripts and press clippings.

When Dr. Oppenheim came to NYU, the School of the Arts had only four departments. Under his leadership, the school quadrupled in size. Dr. Oppenheim retired as Dean in 1991 after 22 years with NYU.
A later accession, 93-025, was added to the collection. Series IV, Development and Series V, Administrative Files are included in this accession. Series V is the largest of the five series.
